name: "Stoic" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Felt pen, paint pen, brush pen, and liner pen on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and color.] This is both my spirit animal (some kind of extinct deer-man-demon) and a psychic self-portrait. I enjoy the strange mood, even if it's a bit somber. ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
